# Figma and UI

For the complete design-analysis, implementation, and visual-verification workflow, use [`figma-to-production`](../../.agents/skills/figma-to-production/SKILL.md).

- Use **design tokens** (CSS variables / Tailwind theme) — avoid one-off hex in many places.
- **Match layout and spacing** from specs; ask if design is ambiguous.
- **Responsive is mandatory** — every screen and component must work on mobile, tablet, and desktop. Prefer mobile-first breakpoints; never ship desktop-only layouts.
- **Accessibility**: semantic HTML, labels, focus states, contrast.
- Prefer **existing UI primitives** in the repo over new ad-hoc styles.
- **Dropdowns / selects:** always use `DarkSelect` (`apps/web/src/shared/ui/dark-select.tsx`). Do **not** ship visible native `<select>` or a one-off dropdown. See ADR-009 in `docs/DECISIONS.md`.
